## Color Psychology & Brand Alignment

### Professional Trust (Blue)
- Conveys reliability, expertise, established business
- Used for main navigation, primary CTAs, trust badges
- Represents 30+ years of experience and licensing

### Warm Approachability (Orange)
- Represents family-owned values and personal service
- Used for secondary CTAs, family story highlights
- Balances professionalism with friendly accessibility

### Clean Professionalism (Grays)
- Represents attention to detail and clean job sites
- Used for body text, backgrounds, subtle elements
- Conveys meticulous craftsmanship and quality work

### Fresh Reliability (White)
- Represents clean, fresh surfaces and new installations
- Used for backgrounds, cards, primary surfaces
- Conveys the transformation from old to new floors

## Accessibility Standards

### Contrast Requirements
- All text combinations meet WCAG AA standards (4.5:1 minimum)
- Primary button text (#ffffff) on primary background (#1e40af) = 8.6:1 ✓
- Body text (#374151) on white background (#ffffff) = 9.6:1 ✓
- Secondary text (#6b7280) on white background (#ffffff) = 4.7:1 ✓

### Color-Blind Considerations
- Never rely on color alone to convey information
- Use icons, text, or patterns alongside color coding
- Test with color blindness simulators during development
- Ensure form validation uses text + color for errors